---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro'
import CodeWindow from '../components/CodeWindow.astro'
---

<Layout
  title="About — Motion Components"
  description="Learn how motion-components is built, what web components are, and how to use the library in your framework.">
  <div class="about-wrap">
    <header class="about-hero">
      <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
      <h1>
        The motion layer<br /> your <motion-liquid text="UI" intensity="12" speed="1.5"
        ></motion-liquid> is missing
      </h1>

      <p class="lead">
        <motion-code-inline copy-visible>motion-components</motion-code-inline> is an open-source library
        of physics-based web components. Drop them into any framework and get smooth, interruptible animation
        out of the box — or extend and compose them to build your own.
      </p>
    </header>

    <!-- ── Manifesto ────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="manifesto">
      <h2 class="manifesto-statement">
        Motion is not only <motion-headline by="chars" interval="0.04" duration="0.9"
          >decoration
        </motion-headline>.</h2
      >

      <p>
        We live in an era of instantaneous interfaces. Pages snap in. Modals appear. Content jumps
        into place. Every interaction is a hard cut — and every hard cut teaches the brain that this
        world has no physics, no weight, no continuity.
      </p>

      <p>
        Motion is the connective tissue of experience. When an element moves with mass — when it
        overshoots and settles, when it carries velocity from one state into the next — it stops
        being a component and starts being something you can trust. Your finger knows the
        difference. Your eye knows the difference.
      </p>
    </section>
    <p>
      motion-components exists because good motion shouldn't require a dedicated animation engineer
      or a working knowledge of bezier curves. It should be a tag you drop in. The physics come
      free.
    </p>

    <p class="tagline">The simplicity of HTML. <span>The power of Motion.</span></p>

    <!-- ── What are web components ─────────── -->
    <section>
      <h2>What are web components?</h2>
      <p>
        Web components are native browser APIs for defining custom HTML elements. A tag like <motion-code-inline
          copy-visible>motion-hover</motion-code-inline
        > is registered once and behaves like any built-in HTML element. All major browsers support them
        without polyfills.
      </p>
      <p>
        Most frameworks work with custom elements, but some require a small amount of configuration
        to prevent their compilers treating unknown tags as errors. See the <a
          href="#framework-setup">framework setup</a
        > section below.
      </p>
      <div class="link-list">
        <a
          href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Web_components"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener">MDN — Web Components guide ↗</a
        >
        <a href="https://caniuse.com/custom-elementsv1" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
          >Can I Use — Custom Elements ↗</a
        >
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── Framework setup ─────────────────── -->
    <section id="framework-setup">
      <h2>Framework setup</h2>

      <h3>Vanilla HTML / Astro / Svelte / SolidJS / Alpine</h3>
      <p>No configuration needed. Import the library once and use the tags directly.</p>
      <CodeWindow filename="app.js" copy code={`import 'motion-components'`} />

      <h3>Vue 3</h3>
      <p>
        Vue's template compiler warns on unknown tags by default. Tell it to treat any <code
          >motion-*</code
        > tag as a custom element:
      </p>
      <CodeWindow
        filename="vite.config.js"
        copy
        code={`import { defineConfig } from 'vite'
import vue from '@vitejs/plugin-vue'

export default defineConfig({
  plugins: [
    vue({
      template: {
        compilerOptions: {
          isCustomElement: tag => tag.startsWith('motion-')
        }
      }
    })
  ]
})`}
      />

      <h3>Angular</h3>
      <p>
        Angular's template compiler errors on unknown elements. Add <code
          >CUSTOM_ELEMENTS_SCHEMA</code
        > to any module or standalone component that uses motion-components:
      </p>
      <CodeWindow
        filename="app.module.ts"
        copy
        code={`import { NgModule, CUSTOM_ELEMENTS_SCHEMA } from '@angular/core'

@NgModule({
  schemas: [CUSTOM_ELEMENTS_SCHEMA]
})
export class AppModule {}`}
      />
      <p>For standalone components:</p>
      <CodeWindow
        filename="app.component.ts"
        copy
        code={`import { Component, CUSTOM_ELEMENTS_SCHEMA } from '@angular/core'

@Component({
  selector: 'app-root',
  standalone: true,
  schemas: [CUSTOM_ELEMENTS_SCHEMA],
  template: \`<motion-hover><button>Hover</button></motion-hover>\`
})
export class AppComponent {}`}
      />

      <h3>React</h3>
      <p>
        React 19 has full custom element support. For React 18 and earlier, boolean attributes and
        custom events require extra handling. Full React wrappers are coming soon.
      </p>
      <CodeWindow
        filename="App.jsx"
        copy
        code={`// React 19+
import 'motion-components'

export function App() {
  return (
    <motion-hover scale="1.08">
      <button>Hover me</button>
    </motion-hover>
  )
}`}
      />
    </section>

    <!-- ── Customising components ──────────── -->
    <section>
      <h2>Customising components</h2>

      <h3>1. HTML attributes</h3>
      <p>
        The primary API is plain HTML attributes. Every tunable value — spring duration, scale,
        direction — is exposed as an attribute with a sensible default.
      </p>
      <CodeWindow
        filename="example.html"
        copy
        code={`<!-- tighter spring, more lift -->
<motion-hover scale="1.08" y="-12" duration="0.2">
  <button>Hover me</button>
</motion-hover>

<!-- reveal from further down, slower -->
<motion-reveal y="48" duration="1.2">
  <h2>Smooth entrance</h2>
</motion-reveal>

<!-- stagger children with custom interval -->
<motion-stagger interval="0.12" duration="0.6">
  <div>One</div>
  <div>Two</div>
  <div>Three</div>
</motion-stagger>`}
      />

      <h3>2. CSS custom properties</h3>
      <p>
        CSS custom properties inherit across the shadow DOM boundary. Components that render visible
        UI expose custom properties you can override from the outside. For example, <motion-code-inline
          copy-visible>motion-code</motion-code-inline
        > exposes syntax highlight tokens:
      </p>
      <CodeWindow
        filename="theme.css"
        copy
        code={`:root {
  --cw-keyword: #c084fc;
  --cw-string:  #86efac;
  --cw-tag:     #67e8f9;
}`}
      />

      <h3>3. Extending components</h3>
      <p
        >Each component is a standard custom element class. Subclass it to change defaults or add
        behaviour:</p
      >
      <CodeWindow
        filename="my-hover.js"
        copy
        code={`import { MotionHover } from 'motion-components'

class MyHover extends MotionHover {
  scale = 1.1

  connectedCallback() {
    super.connectedCallback()
    this.style.cursor = 'pointer'
  }
}

customElements.define('my-hover', MyHover)`}
      />

      <h3>4. Composing primitives</h3>
      <p>Wrap primitives inside each other — they each do one thing and never interfere:</p>
      <CodeWindow
        filename="composed.html"
        copy
        code={`<motion-stagger interval="0.1">
  <motion-hover scale="1.04" y="-6">
    <div class="card">Card one</div>
  </motion-hover>
  <motion-hover scale="1.04" y="-6">
    <div class="card">Card two</div>
  </motion-hover>
  <motion-hover scale="1.04" y="-6">
    <div class="card">Card three</div>
  </motion-hover>
</motion-stagger>`}
      />
    </section>

    <!-- ── Stack ────────────────────────────── -->
    <section>
      <h2>How it's built</h2>
      <p>
        Components are authored with <a href="https://lit.dev" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Lit</a
        > — a small library that adds reactive properties and declarative templates on top of the native
        custom element APIs. Lit is bundled into the output and never appears as a peer dependency.
      </p>
      <p>
        All animations go through <a href="https://motion.dev" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
          >Motion</a
        > — a spring physics animation library. Springs replace cubic-bezier easing curves, so animations
        are naturally interruptible: interrupt one mid-flight and it continues from its current velocity
        rather than snapping.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- ── Philosophy ──────────────────────── -->
    <section>
      <h2>Design philosophy</h2>
      <ul class="philosophy-list">
        <li>
          <strong>Motion-first.</strong> Animation is not a coating applied after the fact — it is a core
          part of how interfaces communicate. Every component is designed from that premise.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>No janky animations.</strong> Springs replace duration-based easing. An interrupted
          spring continues from its current velocity; an interrupted cubic-bezier snaps. The difference
          is felt immediately.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>One responsibility per component.</strong> Primitives do one thing well. Complexity
          comes from composition, not configuration.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Accessibility is not optional.</strong>
          <code>prefers-reduced-motion</code> is checked at the animation layer. Components degrade gracefully
          without any extra work from the consumer.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>
  </div>

  <script>
    import 'motion-components'
  </script>

  <style>
    .about-wrap {
      max-width: 720px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 5rem 2rem 6rem;
    }

    .eyebrow {
      font-size: 0.72rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.14em;
      color: var(--color-accent);
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    h1 {
      font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 6vw, 3.8rem);
      font-weight: 800;
      letter-spacing: -0.04em;
      line-height: 1.05;
      margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    }

    h1 motion-liquid {
      color: var(--color-yellow);
    }

    .lead {
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      color: var(--color-muted);
      line-height: 1.75;
      margin-bottom: 0;
    }

    section {
      margin-top: 3rem;
      padding-top: 3rem;
      border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    }

    .manifesto {
      border-top: none;
      padding-top: 0;
      margin-top: 3rem;
    }

    .manifesto-statement {
      display: block;
      font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 4vw, 2.6rem);
      font-weight: 800;
      letter-spacing: -0.04em;
      line-height: 1.1;
      color: var(--color-text);
      margin-bottom: 1.75rem;
    }

    .manifesto-statement motion-headline {
      color: var(--color-yellow);
      display: inline-block;
    }

    .tagline {
      font-size: clamp(1.3rem, 3vw, 1.7rem);
      font-weight: 800;
      letter-spacing: -0.03em;
      line-height: 1.2;
      color: var(--color-text);
      margin: 2rem 0 0;
    }

    .tagline span {
      color: var(--color-yellow);
    }

    .manifesto p:not(.manifesto-statement) {
      font-size: 1.05rem;
      line-height: 1.8;
      color: var(--color-muted);
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
      max-width: 640px;
    }

    h2 {
      font-size: 1.4rem;
      font-weight: 800;
      letter-spacing: -0.03em;
      margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    }

    h3 {
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      color: var(--color-text);
      margin: 1.75rem 0 0.5rem;
    }

    h3:first-of-type {
      margin-top: 1.25rem;
    }

    p {
      color: var(--color-muted);
      font-size: 0.97rem;
      line-height: 1.75;
      margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    }

    p:last-child {
      margin-bottom: 0;
    }

    a {
      color: var(--color-accent);
      text-decoration: none;
    }

    a:hover {
      text-decoration: underline;
    }

    ul {
      color: var(--color-muted);
      font-size: 0.97rem;
      line-height: 1.75;
      padding-left: 1.25rem;
      margin: 0.75rem 0 1rem;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 0.5rem;
    }

    ul li strong {
      color: var(--color-text);
    }

    code {
      font-family: var(--font-mono);
      font-size: 0.85em;
      color: var(--color-accent);
      background: var(--color-accent-dim);
      padding: 0.1em 0.4em;
      border-radius: 4px;
    }

    .link-list {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 0.4rem;
      margin-top: 1rem;
    }

    .link-list a {
      font-size: 0.88rem;
      font-weight: 500;
    }

    .philosophy-list {
      list-style: none;
      padding: 0;
      gap: 0.75rem;
    }

    .philosophy-list li {
      padding: 0.875rem 1.1rem;
      background: var(--color-surface);
      border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      border-radius: 10px;
      font-size: 0.95rem;
    }

    motion-code {
      display: block;
      margin: 0.75rem 0 1.25rem;
    }
  </style>
</Layout>
